@page "/"


<div class="mdc-layout-grid__cell--span-12">
    <MTCard>
        <Primary>
            <div class="bmdc-card__primary">
                <h1 class="bmdc-card__title mdc-typography--headline4">Welcome to Blazor MDC</h1>
                <h2 class="bmdc-card__title mdc-typography--subtitle1">Demonstration website</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="bmdc-card__secondary">
                <ul class="mdc-typography--body2 point-list">
                    <li>
                        Blazor MDC is a <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/razor-pages/ui-class?view=aspnetcore-3.1&tabs=visual-studio" target="_blank">Razor Class Library</a>
                        for <a href="https://dotnet.microsoft.com/apps/aspnet/web-apps/blazor" target="_blank">Blazor</a> apps bringing a comprehensive, lightweight suite of <a href="https://material.io" target="_blank">Material Theme</a> components.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Use the <a href="https://www.nuget.org/packages/BlazorMdc/" target="_blank">nuget package</a> - use the version 1.0.0 latest pre-release.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        You will notice that page transitions are animated with a fade out/in effect using the <a href="https://blazormdc.com/docs/BlazorMdc/Model/AnimatedNavigation/IMTAnimatedNavigationManager.cs.html" target="_blank">Blazor MDC Animated Navigation Manager</a>;
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Blazor MDC has been built by <a href="https://dioptra.tech" target="_blank">Simon Ziegler of Dioptra</a> and <a href="https://www.optimiumhealth.com/" target="_blank">Mark Stega of Optimium Health</a>, and is licensed under the permissive
                        <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MIT_License" target="_blank">MIT License</a> and is delivered as a <a href="https://www.nuget.org/packages/BlazorMdc/" target="_blank">Nuget package</a>.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        One of Material Theme's benefits is the ability to theme, using either SASS mixins (preferred and more capable) or CSS variables. We have four SASS mixin driven themes on 
                        this website which you can select from a menu when you click the action button on the far right of the top app bar. Look particularly at how these four themes affect
                        buttons and text fields. <a href="https://blazormdc.com/docs" target="_blank">See the docs</a> for more detail on how to theme. This site's theming can be found in
                        <a href="https://github.com/BlazorMdc/BlazorMdc/tree/develop/BlazorMdcWebsite.Components/Styles" target="_blank">the GitHub repository</a>, and you can see how we
                        use simple Node commands in <a href="https://github.com/BlazorMdc/BlazorMdc/blob/develop/BlazorMdcWebsite.Components/package.json" target="_blank">package.json</a>, called from
                        build actions in <a href="https://github.com/BlazorMdc/BlazorMdc/blob/main/BlazorMdcWebsite.Components/BlazorMdcWebsite.Components.csproj#L25" target="_blank">the CSPROJ file</a>.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        This website is currently executing on <strong>@Runtime</strong> hosted by <strong>@OSDescription/@OSArchitecture</strong> built in <strong>@BuildMode</strong> mode.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </Primary>
    </MTCard>
</div>



